WEBVTT

00:02.200 --> 00:04.396
[♪♪♪]

00:04.600 --> 00:07.434
ANNOUNCER:
<i>This is the story of two sisters,</i>

00:08.080 --> 00:11.437
<i>Jessica Tate and Mary Campbell.</i>

00:11.680 --> 00:15.993
<i>Jessica lives in a neighbourhood</i>
<i>known as rich.</i>

00:16.200 --> 00:17.759
<i>Jessica likes life.</i>

00:18.000 --> 00:20.834
<i>The only thing about life</i>
<i>she would change, if she could,</i>

00:21.040 --> 00:23.509
<i>is that she would</i>
<i>set it all to music.</i>

00:24.760 --> 00:28.390
<i>The Tates have more secrets</i>
<i>than they do money.</i>

00:31.320 --> 00:34.392
<i>We're approaching</i>
<i>Mary Campbell's house.</i>

00:36.240 --> 00:37.754
<i>Mary, too, likes life.</i>

00:37.960 --> 00:41.749
<i>Unfortunately, life doesn't seem to be</i>
<i>too crazy about her.</i>

00:41.960 --> 00:44.191
<i>As you can see,</i>
<i>the Campbells don't have</i>

00:44.400 --> 00:46.756
<i>nearly as much money</i>
<i>as the Tates.</i>

00:47.600 --> 00:51.230
<i>They do, however,</i>
<i>have as many secrets.</i>

00:54.920 --> 00:58.516
<i>In last week's episode of</i> Soap,
<i>we discovered that not only Jessica</i>

00:58.720 --> 01:01.474
<i>and her daughter are having an affair</i>
<i>with Peter, the tennis pro,</i>

01:01.680 --> 01:03.990
<i>but that Peter is Burt Campbell's</i>
<i>long-lost son.</i>

01:04.200 --> 01:06.396
<i>As for Burt Campbell,</i>
<i>Mary's second husband,</i>

01:06.600 --> 01:09.752
<i>he is so overwhelmed by guilt</i>
<i>for having murdered Mary's</i>
<i>first husband,</i>

01:09.960 --> 01:11.599
<i>he can no longer</i>
<i>make love to her.</i>

01:11.800 --> 01:15.714
<i>But this is nothing, because Burt</i>
<i>doesn't know that Mary's son Danny,</i>

01:15.920 --> 01:19.436
<i>in order to leave the Mob, has to</i>
<i>kill the man who killed his father.</i>

01:19.640 --> 01:22.633
<i>Danny doesn't know that</i>
<i>that man is Burt yet.</i>

01:22.960 --> 01:26.590
<i>Mary's other son, Jodie,</i>
<i>is contemplating becoming</i>
<i>her daughter.</i>

01:26.960 --> 01:30.670
<i>Life is also not exactly a bed of roses</i>
<i>for Jessica's husband, Chester.</i>

01:30.880 --> 01:33.839
<i>His affair with his secretary, Claire,</i>
<i>has become complicated</i>

01:34.040 --> 01:36.191
<i>by the fact that</i>
<i>she is now blackmailing him.</i>

01:36.400 --> 01:40.997
<i>Confused? You won't be after</i>
<i>this week's episode of</i> Soap.

01:42.400 --> 01:44.710
<i>We begin this week's</i>
<i>episode of</i> Soap

01:44.920 --> 01:48.516
<i>shortly after Peter's arrival</i>
<i>at the Tate home.</i>

01:50.840 --> 01:52.718
I just can't believe it!

01:52.920 --> 01:54.832
I cannot believe it.

01:55.040 --> 01:57.839
I mean, it's such a small,
small world. I can't get over it.

01:58.040 --> 02:00.874
I mean, my long-lost son
from Hawaii

02:01.080 --> 02:03.356
comes to Connecticut
and winds up teaching

02:03.560 --> 02:06.234
my sister-in-law
and her daughter tennis.

02:06.440 --> 02:08.556
Bet that ain't all he teaches.

02:09.160 --> 02:11.470
And then, and this is
really incredible,

02:11.680 --> 02:13.956
my sister-in-law
and her daughter don't know

02:14.160 --> 02:15.753
they have the same
tennis teacher.

02:15.960 --> 02:18.634
Plus, which he doesn't know,
they're mother and daughter. Pfft!

02:19.360 --> 02:21.670
I'm not finished with that,
Benson.

02:24.280 --> 02:27.398
And then... And then
to top it all off,

02:27.600 --> 02:31.480
no one, but no one knows
he's my son. Pfft!

02:31.720 --> 02:33.598
So what, Burt?

02:35.720 --> 02:39.157
So it's a small, small world,
and I can't get over it, can you?

02:39.360 --> 02:40.953
Yes.

02:41.600 --> 02:45.037
Colonel, where's
General Eisenhower?
Wasn't he invited?

02:45.720 --> 02:47.359
Where in the world is Jessica?

02:47.560 --> 02:50.837
In my kitchen, and I wish she
would get the hell out of there.

02:52.080 --> 02:54.356
I'll get her, Chester.
Eat your dinner.

02:54.720 --> 02:57.110
Benson, I am not finished.

