make a soufflé for dessert.

03:22.040 --> 03:25.511
Uh-uh, uh-uh. Forget it.
I ain't making no soufflé.

03:25.720 --> 03:28.872
I told you I ain't making
no soufflé for these animals.

03:29.080 --> 03:33.438
The way they eat, I ought to just
shove the food in under the door.

03:33.960 --> 03:36.429
And you see, for a soufflé,
of course, you have to beat

03:36.640 --> 03:38.438
the egg whites and the
egg yolks separately,

03:38.640 --> 03:40.233
Therefore, you need
two people, Mary.

03:40.440 --> 03:43.601
I mean, one to beat the whites
and one to beat the yolks.
I'm beating the whites.

03:43.800 --> 03:48.352
Oh, yeah? Well, there's
a whole table of them in there
I'd like to help you with.

03:50.720 --> 03:52.916
Jessie, I know.

03:53.280 --> 03:55.954
And if you don't come out,
everyone's going to be suspicious.

03:56.160 --> 03:58.914
Oh, Mary, I'm so
ashamed I could die.

03:59.160 --> 04:02.756
Do you realise what I've done?
I've had an affair with my nephew.

04:02.960 --> 04:05.270
I think that's against the law.

04:05.480 --> 04:06.834
He's not your nephew.

04:07.040 --> 04:12.115
I mean, I just got used to adultery
and now I have to get used to, uh...

04:12.840 --> 04:14.638
Incest.

04:16.160 --> 04:19.551
Benson, he is not related to us.
He is my stepson.

04:21.680 --> 04:23.160
Oh, Mary,

04:23.800 --> 04:27.396
I've never done this
before, ever. I...

04:28.000 --> 04:30.754
See, what it was, was...

04:30.960 --> 04:32.952
I was lonely.

04:33.160 --> 04:37.712
I mean, uh, Chester's never here,
and then the kids are never here,

04:37.920 --> 04:43.075
and I've done all the clever things
I could with shelving paper, and, uh...

04:44.680 --> 04:49.709
So, Mary, I did that.

04:49.920 --> 04:52.640
But I'm never gonna
do it again, Mary. Ever.

04:52.920 --> 04:55.230
Okay, Jessie. Okay.

04:55.440 --> 04:56.476
Come on out, now.

04:56.680 --> 04:59.718
If you stay in here,
Chester will become suspicious.

04:59.920 --> 05:02.754
Oh, my God! Chester.
I have to tell him.

05:02.960 --> 05:04.792
Mary, I have to tell
Chester what I've done.

05:05.000 --> 05:07.469
Are you crazy?
No, it's the right thing to do.

05:07.680 --> 05:09.751
It's the stupid thing to do.

05:10.800 --> 05:12.154
I'm going to tell him.

05:12.360 --> 05:14.920
All right, Jessie.
I was never gonna tell you this,

05:15.200 --> 05:18.591
but poor, sweet Chester has been...
Hm?

05:19.800 --> 05:23.237
How do I put this?
Jumping on anything that breathes?

05:26.200 --> 05:27.680
[LAUGHS]

05:29.560 --> 05:33.110
I wasn't gonna put it
quite that way.

05:33.600 --> 05:36.035
Oh, sweet, adorable Mary.

05:36.240 --> 05:38.550
I mean, you'd just do
anything to keep me
from telling him.

05:38.760 --> 05:41.798
Even to making up that
outrageous lie about Chester.

05:42.000 --> 05:43.673
Hi, Ma. Hi, Aunt Mary.
JESSICA: Oh, hello darling.

05:43.880 --> 05:45.600
Can I have the keys
to the car? It's locked.

05:45.800 --> 05:46.950
But you don't drive, dear.

05:47.160 --> 05:50.232
I don't want them for driving.
I want them for parking.

05:50.440 --> 05:52.591
The car is parked already.

05:52.800 --> 05:55.554
Look, Ma. Can I just
have the keys?

05:55.760 --> 05:58.480
I got my date outside
and we just want to sit in it.

05:58.680 --> 06:00.637
But, dear,
you can invite her in.

06:00.840 --> 06:02.797
I mean, she doesn't
have to sit in the car.

06:03.400 --> 06:05.232
She likes sitting in cars.

06:06.640 --> 06:09.678
Ma, we're just gonna listen
to the tape deck and talk.
I promise.

06:09.880 --> 06:12.873
Oh, well, all right.
Here you are.

06:13.080 --> 06:15.356
Thanks, Ma. Bye, Aunt Mary.
MARY: Bye.

06:15.560 --> 06:19.679
Ah, children. I mean,
you work, work, work to
give them a beautiful house,

06:19.880 --> 06:22.076
and then they just
want to sit in the car.

06:22.840 --> 06:25.594
Jessica?
Oh. Mary.

06:25.800 --> 06:27.792
Well, this is a fine how-do-you-do.

06:28.000 --> 06:30.595
You invite your insane family
over for dinner,

06:30.800 --> 06:32.280
and I'm the one
who's stuck with them.

06:32.440 --> 06:37.231
Now, Jessica, either you get out
of this kitchen and come inside,
or I am sending everyone home.

06:37.440 --> 06:38.715
Send them home.

06:39.960 --> 06:41.917
Shut up, Benson.

06:42.640 --> 06:44.552
I will, when you send them home.

06:45.920 --> 06:47.673
Well, Jessica?

06:47.960 --> 06:50.111
What were the choices again?

06:51.280 --> 06:52.839
Come on, Jessica.

06:54.640 --> 06:57.758
It's a small, small world
and I can't get over it.

06:57.960 --> 06:59.314
Why don't you try, Burt?

06:59.520 --> 07:01.079
[LAUGHS]

07:01.280 --> 07:03.961
You know, it's funny.
I've been thinking about
taking tennis lessons.

07:04.040 --> 07:07.636
Get your hands off
my son, you fruit.

07:07.840 --> 07:10.799
My brother is not a fruit!

07:11.000 --> 07:13.276
JESSICA:
Oh, Mary!

07:14.080 --> 07:17.391
Boys! Stop it! That's enough.
JESSICA: Mary!

07:19.440 --> 07:23.559
I am not cleaning this.
Ain't no way I'm gonna
clean this.

07:24.040 --> 07:26.999
Burt, stop this, you idiot! Oh!

07:30.320 --> 07:33.233
Medic, medic! I've been shot.

07:35.960 --> 07:38.316
Drop that, you thug.

07:40.280 --> 07:42.840
Good night, Uncle Chester.
I had a wonderful time.

07:43.440 --> 07:46.831
I've had it. I've had it
with all of you. You are
never coming here again!

07:47.040 --> 07:49.350
Terrific. Nothing could
suit me better.

07:49.640 --> 07:50.790
Slobs.

07:51.000 --> 07:53.276
Slobs? Slobs? Heh-heh-heh.

07:53.800 --> 07:55.393
I'm a slob? Look at you.

07:55.600 --> 07:58.274
You've got cranberry sauce
all over your shirt.

07:59.280 --> 08:00.634
Out! Out!

08:01.040 --> 08:02.997
[♪♪♪]

08:13.520 --> 08:14.920
Burt, are you asleep?

08:15.360 --> 08:18.512
Are you kidding? With that
racket going on next door?

08:19.080 --> 08:21.390
Burt, we don't even try anymore.

08:21.600 --> 08:22.716
Why don't we try?

08:22.920 --> 08:24.832
1:00 in the morning
and that's going on.

08:25.040 --> 08:26.838
There's nothing going on
next door, Burt.

08:27.040 --> 08:29.839
What, are you joking? You don't
hear that? Farkus and his wife?

08:30.040 --> 08:32.350
Is it that you're not
attracted to me? Is that it?

08:32.559 --> 08:33.880
I think he hit her.

08:34.080 --> 08:36.720
There's nothing
going on next door, Burt.

08:36.919 --> 08:39.879
Did you hear that smack?
Didn't that smack sound
just like a hit?

08:40.080 --> 08:41.753
I didn't hear a hit, Burt.

08:41.960 --> 08:44.998
I didn't hear a smack
and I didn't hear a hit.

08:45.480 --> 08:47.437
[MOUTHING]

08:49.520 --> 08:51.876
What?
I was testing. You didn't hear that?

08:52.080 --> 08:53.560
Burt...
Mary, Mary, I think you should

08:53.760 --> 08:57.231
have your ears checked.
It's probably just wax, but I would
have them checked anyway.

08:57.440 --> 09:00.911
Burt, what is it? Is it that
you're not attracted to me?

09:01.520 --> 09:03.876
No. It's a temporary thing.
It'll go away.

09:04.080 --> 09:05.639
It happens to men.

09:05.960 --> 09:07.599
It's been six months.

09:07.800 --> 09:11.396
Oh, wonderful, wonderful.
Put pressure on me, Mary,
it'll never happen.

09:11.600 --> 09:14.911
Pressure? We've never even
talked about it.

09:15.280 --> 09:17.840
I just don't think we can
let this go on forever.

09:18.040 --> 09:19.679
Oh, time.
Now we have time limits?

09:19.880 --> 09:22.121
If there's one thing that
doesn't help, it's time limits.

09:22.320 --> 09:24.437
Darling, maybe you
ought to see a psychiatrist.

09:24.640 --> 09:26.960
Now I'm crazy, right?
All of a sudden,
I'm some kind of nut.

09:27.160 --> 09:30.119
No, darling, I just thought maybe
it might help to talk to someone...

09:30.320 --> 09:34.678
Did you hear them? Quiet.
Human beings are trying
to sleep up here!

09:35.200 --> 09:37.510
Burt, are you having an affair?

09:39.960 --> 09:43.397
God, Mary, no!
Because it's normal, darling.

09:43.600 --> 09:47.753
A chance encounter,
a few glorious stolen moments,

09:47.960 --> 09:50.600
and sometimes,
life can be all the richer for it.

09:50.800 --> 09:53.520
So if you're having an affair,
you can tell me.

09:53.720 --> 09:56.997
I'll understand.
Mary, I swear it. There's no one.

09:57.560 --> 10:01.031
Good. Because if you were,
I'd rip your heart out.

10:01.800 --> 10:04.031
Mary, how could you think that,
even for a minute?

10:04.240 --> 10:07.278
Burt, I bought something today.

10:07.480 --> 10:10.518
I think it might help. Now...

10:11.280 --> 10:13.556
Don't let the title
frighten you.

10:19.640 --> 10:21.757
<i>The Cookbook of Sex?</i>

10:21.960 --> 10:23.917
I know.
I wish they hadn't called it that.

10:24.120 --> 10:28.512
But, look, it's written by an M.D.
Recipes? He gives recipes?

10:28.720 --> 10:30.712
Mary, you actually
paid money for this?

10:30.920 --> 10:32.559
Well, yes.

10:32.760 --> 10:34.399
I mean, I've tried everything.

10:34.600 --> 10:36.831
I've tried short nightgowns,
long nightgowns,

10:37.040 --> 10:38.918
new nightgowns, no nightgowns.

10:39.200 --> 10:42.432
I have powdered myself,
perfumed myself.

10:42.640 --> 10:45.474
Bees are attracted to me
and you're not.

10:46.240 --> 10:48.197
Mary, Mary, don't cry.

10:48.400 --> 10:51.154
Please, honey, don't cry.
Please, don't cry.

10:51.360 --> 10:52.840
I just feel awful.

10:53.040 --> 10:55.600
Sweetheart, it's not you,
I swear it. I...

10:55.800 --> 10:57.439
Look, I...

10:57.640 --> 10:58.710
Bzz. Bzz.

10:58.920 --> 11:01.071
I love you,
and you're all I want.

11:01.280 --> 11:03.112
I promise you,
if things don't change,

11:03.320 --> 11:07.030
I'll get some help.
I promise. Okay?

11:07.240 --> 11:08.515
Bzz.

11:09.680 --> 11:11.433
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

11:14.720 --> 11:17.235
Try and get some sleep, Mary.

11:23.160 --> 11:25.038
Look at that.

11:25.240 --> 11:27.835
I mean, that's a total
impossibility.

11:29.800 --> 11:32.759
I mean, the Flying Wallendas,
at the height of their career,

11:32.960 --> 11:34.917
couldn't get
into a position like that.

11:35.120 --> 11:37.077
[♪♪♪]

11:39.280 --> 11:41.237
[♪♪♪]

11:42.240 --> 11:46.234
Claire! What are you doing,
calling me at home?

11:46.960 --> 11:49.475
For crying out loud, Claire,
it's 1:00 in the morning.

11:49.680 --> 11:51.990
I can't come over.

11:52.200 --> 11:55.716
All right, Claire.
All right. I'll come over.

11:55.920 --> 11:57.991
I'll think of a way. Goodbye.

12:00.000 --> 12:01.673
Who's laughing?

12:03.160 --> 12:05.197
Benson, is that you laughing?

12:06.160 --> 12:07.160
Oh!

12:07.320 --> 12:10.358
What?
I was just surprised to see you.

12:11.600 --> 12:12.920
I live here.

12:13.520 --> 12:15.830
No, I mean still up.

12:16.040 --> 12:18.680
I thought maybe
you had gone to sleep by now.

12:19.760 --> 12:21.353
I had a business call.

12:22.960 --> 12:26.237
Chester, I have a confession
to make. I, uh...

12:26.440 --> 12:28.432
Chester, please sit down.

12:28.640 --> 12:30.438
What is it, Jessica?

12:30.960 --> 12:34.317
Chester, when people
have been married a long time,

12:34.520 --> 12:36.273
they spend a lot of time
together,

12:36.480 --> 12:38.360
and so then they get
kind of used to each other.

12:38.440 --> 12:41.240
And then, of course, on the other
hand, they spend a lot of time apart,

12:41.320 --> 12:43.198
and so they don't see
each other very much.

12:43.720 --> 12:45.837
So sometimes
they tend to get lonely,

12:46.040 --> 12:48.794
and sometimes, Chester,
despite themselves,

12:49.000 --> 12:51.640
they seek some
little comfort elsewhere.

12:52.480 --> 12:55.314
And so, Chester,
what I'm trying to say is that

12:55.520 --> 12:59.196
sometimes home cooking is boring,
and sometimes the kitchen is closed.

12:59.400 --> 13:03.076
And so, sometimes
one goes out to eat.

13:03.960 --> 13:06.759
Jessica!
Oh, Chester.

13:06.960 --> 13:08.519
Jessie!

13:08.720 --> 13:11.918
Oh, dear God, Jessica!
You're not saying...

13:12.120 --> 13:13.120
I am.

13:13.320 --> 13:16.119
After all these years,
I thought I knew you.

13:16.320 --> 13:18.880
I know, Chester, I know.
How could you?

13:19.080 --> 13:21.754
I don't know, Chester.
I don't know.

13:23.280 --> 13:26.352
How could you?
How could you?
Even for a minute.

13:26.560 --> 13:28.153
Oh, I'm sorry, Chester.

13:28.360 --> 13:32.673
How could you think,
even for a second,
that I would be unfaithful?

13:33.400 --> 13:34.834
Huh?

13:35.360 --> 13:37.920
Do you think our marriage
means nothing to me, Jessica?

13:38.120 --> 13:39.873
Do you think I took
those vows lightly?

13:40.080 --> 13:43.152
I don't believe this.
To accuse me of...

13:43.360 --> 13:45.477
No, no, no, Chester.
I didn't accuse you.

13:45.720 --> 13:47.677
Please, Jessica,
you did accuse me.

13:47.880 --> 13:50.759
No, Chester, I, uh...
Unfaithful!

13:50.960 --> 13:53.475
Me? Jessica,

13:53.680 --> 13:58.709
may I lose the use of the entire
right side of my body

13:58.920 --> 14:02.800
if ever I have so much
as looked at another woman.

14:03.000 --> 14:08.200
May my postnasal drip
back up and drown my brain

14:09.280 --> 14:11.795
if ever I have been
unfaithful to you.

14:12.000 --> 14:15.038
Chester, where are you going?
Out.

14:15.240 --> 14:18.039
You've gotten me
much too upset to sleep.

14:22.840 --> 14:24.797
[♪♪♪]

14:28.640 --> 14:29.960
Hold it!

14:31.520 --> 14:33.352
Put that down.

14:36.960 --> 14:39.919
You understand, don't you,
that this is the last food fight?

14:40.240 --> 14:41.993
I'm making you
a promise right now.

14:42.200 --> 14:45.637
If I ever see one speck of food
anywhere except on a plate,

14:45.840 --> 14:48.116
I am leaving for good.

14:49.080 --> 14:50.514
Clean up this mess.

14:55.640 --> 14:59.270
You want a fresh cup of coffee?
I think you got some banana in yours.

15:00.080 --> 15:02.072
Yeah, thanks.

15:03.960 --> 15:05.633
You know, I think
she's really serious.

15:05.840 --> 15:07.399
Yeah, me too.

15:07.600 --> 15:11.389
You see, oddly enough,
the thing is, I don't actually hate you.

15:11.600 --> 15:14.115
I'm not too crazy about you,
but I don't hate you.

15:14.320 --> 15:15.320
It's not even dislike.

15:15.480 --> 15:18.560
I don't dislike you.
Not that I like you, don't get
me wrong, I don't like you.

15:18.720 --> 15:22.396
But I probably could like you
if we didn't hate each other so much.

15:22.600 --> 15:25.752
The thing is,
I don't know why you hate me.

15:26.160 --> 15:27.992
You know something,
neither do I.

15:28.200 --> 15:30.157
I mean, I've thought
about it a lot too.

15:30.400 --> 15:33.552
I've tried coming up with reasons,
but there aren't any.

15:33.760 --> 15:36.719
I just look at you
and I hate your guts.

15:36.920 --> 15:39.435
Yeah, well,
I can understand that.

15:39.680 --> 15:42.673
But you know something?
You've never really done anything.

15:42.880 --> 15:44.439
Danny, it's okay.
Don't worry about it.

15:44.640 --> 15:46.472
I just don't want you to take
the fact that I hate you personally.

15:46.680 --> 15:50.515
I don't. I don't, really.
Danny, I know I annoy you.

15:50.720 --> 15:52.871
I can be a very annoying person.

15:53.080 --> 15:55.197
Like the way I'm always
telling you to leave the Mob.

15:55.400 --> 15:58.040
I mean, if you want to ruin your life
working for a bunch of gangsters...

15:58.240 --> 16:01.153
Well, the fact is,
I'm leaving the Mob.

16:01.920 --> 16:03.354
Danny, that's... When?

16:03.560 --> 16:07.110
Well, soon. There's something
they want me to do for them,
and then I can go.

16:07.320 --> 16:09.039
What do you gotta do?

16:09.320 --> 16:13.109
Nothing. It's just a thing.
I don't even know all the details yet.

16:13.640 --> 16:16.997
Yeah, well, if I can help,
just say the word.

16:18.360 --> 16:19.714
Yeah, Danny, really.

16:20.240 --> 16:21.833
Thanks.

16:22.640 --> 16:25.200
Well, I gotta go. I got a meeting.
We'll see you later?

16:25.400 --> 16:27.960
Right. Bye, Burt.

16:28.160 --> 16:29.879
Bye, Danny.

16:32.680 --> 16:34.000
Burt...

16:34.760 --> 16:36.274
have a nice day.

16:37.480 --> 16:39.073
You too.

16:42.240 --> 16:43.720
Hey, come on.

16:43.920 --> 16:46.276
I'd say things are definitely
improving here.

16:46.480 --> 16:48.836
Danny and I are
becoming buddies.

16:49.040 --> 16:50.952
You know, you go
fishing with a buddy.

16:51.240 --> 16:54.119
And my son Peter is here.
We could go fishing.

16:54.320 --> 16:56.915
Peter could go fishing with
Danny and me. The three
of us could go fishing.

16:57.120 --> 16:58.554
Peter, Danny and me.

16:58.960 --> 17:01.680
And Mary could come.
It'd be just like a real family.

17:02.880 --> 17:04.872
I better buy four
new fishing poles.

17:05.200 --> 17:06.839
Why four new fishing poles, Burt?

17:07.040 --> 17:09.794
I mean, aren't you going
to invite me? I love to fish.

17:10.000 --> 17:12.992
Oh, this is very nice, Burt.
Ever think of wearing a bib
when you eat?

17:13.200 --> 17:15.112
Go away from me, fruit.

17:15.359 --> 17:18.194
"Fruit"! Wonderful.

17:18.560 --> 17:20.472
You've agreed
to stop throwing it.

17:20.680 --> 17:22.911
Don't you think you could
agree to stop saying it?

17:23.160 --> 17:25.277
Can't the two of you
work things out?

17:25.480 --> 17:27.915
Hey, I'd be very willing,
except there's one slight problem.

17:28.119 --> 17:29.190
The man hates me.

17:29.400 --> 17:31.119
He doesn't hate you.

17:31.320 --> 17:34.438
You don't hate him.
Well, close.

17:35.960 --> 17:37.838
Why?
I don't know.

17:38.040 --> 17:39.156
It's because I'm gay.
Right, Burt?

17:39.360 --> 17:41.079
I mean, you hate me
because I'm gay. Right?

17:42.520 --> 17:44.034
Well?

17:44.960 --> 17:47.270
I guess if you need a reason,
that's a good one.

17:47.640 --> 17:50.109
Burt, it's a terrible reason.
I mean, look at me.

17:50.320 --> 17:51.800
I'm a person.

17:52.040 --> 17:54.111
Burt, look at him.

17:54.360 --> 17:56.317
[MOUTHING]

18:04.280 --> 18:06.272
Ugh.

18:07.520 --> 18:08.840
He gives me the creeps.

18:09.040 --> 18:11.111
Burt, what do you mean,
I give you the creeps?

18:11.320 --> 18:13.596
I don't know. You're spooky.

18:13.800 --> 18:16.952
He is not spooky.
I do not find him
in the least spooky.

18:17.160 --> 18:18.799
Yeah, well, maybe you're used to it.

18:19.000 --> 18:21.435
Burt, just think of me
as a person, that's all.

18:21.640 --> 18:24.439
I mean, that's all I am.
I'm a person sitting here.

18:24.640 --> 18:26.677
Burt, look at me.
I'm a person...

18:28.760 --> 18:30.080
who happens to like men.

18:30.320 --> 18:31.515
[WHIMPERS]

18:31.720 --> 18:33.632
MARY: Burt!
Now, wait a minute.

18:33.840 --> 18:38.312
I don't know. I mean, it's...
It's hard, this gay business.
I'm not used to it.

18:38.520 --> 18:40.557
I mean, all my life,
I was never around them.

18:40.760 --> 18:42.717
When I was growing up,
gay meant happy.

18:43.400 --> 18:45.392
I mean, it's just hard
to get used to.

18:45.920 --> 18:48.116
And life was a lot easier then.

18:48.960 --> 18:51.714
I mean, maybe when you
guys were still in the closet,

18:51.920 --> 18:55.550
maybe it wasn't easy on you,
but it was a hell of a lot easier on us.

18:55.760 --> 18:58.800
I mean, used to be, you walked
down the street, a guy smiled,
you smiled back.

18:58.880 --> 19:02.635
Today you smile back,
either you're arrested
or invited dancing.

19:04.080 --> 19:06.914
So it takes getting used to.
It's hard getting used to a guy

19:07.120 --> 19:08.759
who likes guys and not girls.

19:08.960 --> 19:11.520
And now you're gonna
get a sex-change operation
and be a girl.

19:11.720 --> 19:13.951
Now I gotta get used to
a guy who is now a girl

19:14.160 --> 19:17.517
who likes guys and not girls,
who used to be a guy
who liked guys and not girls.

19:17.720 --> 19:19.313
[MUTTERS]

19:21.080 --> 19:24.357
But I'll try.

19:26.200 --> 19:30.717
From now on, I'll try
to look at you as a person.

19:31.360 --> 19:33.511
And I'll try and look at you
the same way.

19:33.960 --> 19:35.917
[♪♪♪]

19:40.640 --> 19:42.916
Danny? Danny.
Come in, come in.

19:43.120 --> 19:44.120
Afternoon, Godfather.

19:44.320 --> 19:46.710
Ah, Danny, sit down.
The food is getting cold.

19:46.920 --> 19:48.957
Godfather, I've given it
a lot of thought...

19:49.160 --> 19:50.833
Not until you taste this, Danny.

19:51.040 --> 19:53.316
Just wait until you taste this.

19:53.520 --> 19:55.273
Oh, no, thanks.
I'm not really very hungry.

19:55.520 --> 19:58.752
Danny, this restaurant
belongs to my mother.

19:58.960 --> 20:01.395
If you don't eat,
she'll kill me, huh?

20:01.600 --> 20:03.239
Okay, but just a little.
All right.

20:03.440 --> 20:05.238
You're gonna love this.
You're gonna love it.

20:05.440 --> 20:09.719
Godfather, I've thought
it over, and I've decided
to take the contract.

20:09.920 --> 20:11.274
How is that, huh?

20:11.480 --> 20:13.870
Oh, it looks great. I love chicken.

20:14.560 --> 20:15.596
That's eel.

20:18.960 --> 20:20.440
It's good, eh? Huh?

20:20.640 --> 20:22.359
Ah! Yes.

20:23.320 --> 20:26.154
And now, I want you to try
some of this linguini.

20:26.360 --> 20:29.080
I swear it's better than sex.

20:29.280 --> 20:33.672
You know, I'm not particularly crazy
about the idea of killing a man.

20:33.880 --> 20:35.394
Who is?

20:35.600 --> 20:37.876
I mean, I have a tough time
killing a bug.

20:38.080 --> 20:42.313
But I think if I have to kill
somebody, I can kill the man
who killed my father.

20:42.960 --> 20:44.076
No, Danny. No, no.

20:44.280 --> 20:47.478
You gotta twirl the linguini
around the spoon like this.

20:49.400 --> 20:52.791
Danny, you can't sit there
with the linguini hanging
out of your mouth.

20:53.000 --> 20:54.434
You look like, uh,

20:54.640 --> 20:56.279
a demented walrus.

20:56.480 --> 20:57.755
[CHUCKLES]

20:57.960 --> 20:59.440
That's better.

21:00.160 --> 21:02.197
So now will you tell me
who killed my father?

21:02.400 --> 21:05.438
Okay. I'm gonna tell you.
The man who killed your
father was...

21:05.640 --> 21:06.835
[SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

21:09.960 --> 21:11.713
Some surprise, eh?

21:12.320 --> 21:13.993
What? I didn't hear what you said.

21:14.200 --> 21:16.669
I said, some surprise, eh?

21:17.800 --> 21:20.395
No, the name.
Oh.

21:20.600 --> 21:22.159
Your stepfather.

21:23.400 --> 21:25.119
What about my stepfather?

21:25.360 --> 21:26.840
He's the one.
Burt?

21:27.040 --> 21:29.839
Oh, yes, Burt.
Oh, come on. Be serious.

21:30.040 --> 21:32.191
Oh, you think I make it up,
huh, Danny?

21:32.400 --> 21:35.996
You think I make up a story
your stepfather kills your father
and now you gotta...

21:36.200 --> 21:40.831
Hey, Shakespeare maybe makes up
bad stories like that. I don't, Danny.

21:42.040 --> 21:43.759
But why would he kill my father?

21:43.960 --> 21:46.839
Because your father was trying
to run him out of business.

21:47.040 --> 21:50.272
If I was Burt,
I would do the same thing.

21:50.520 --> 21:53.718
Now, I love your father,
Danny, but a sweet man?

21:54.000 --> 21:55.559
No.

21:57.120 --> 21:58.349
I can't believe this.

21:58.680 --> 22:02.754
Oh. In the meantime,
the saltimbocca is
ice-cold, Danny.

22:02.960 --> 22:05.191
Burt?
Yes, Burt. Now, look, look.

22:05.400 --> 22:07.480
You didn't touch a thing.
My mother is gonna kill me.

22:07.720 --> 22:09.632
Burt Campbell killed my father?

22:09.840 --> 22:12.912
There are two things in this life
that my mother can't stand to see.

22:13.120 --> 22:16.909
A guest host on the <i>Tonight Show</i>
and food left on a plate.

22:17.880 --> 22:19.439
Huh?

22:20.920 --> 22:23.992
Maybe it was another
Burt Campbell.
It's a common name.

22:24.200 --> 22:26.840
Danny, it was him.
He was the one.

22:27.040 --> 22:29.953
No, hey, this is for you.

22:33.120 --> 22:34.520
There's a gun in there.

22:34.720 --> 22:37.872
Oh, and what did you think
would be in there, spumoni to go, eh?

22:38.360 --> 22:39.760
Come on, Danny.

22:42.200 --> 22:43.759
I can't do it.

22:44.720 --> 22:45.836
I beg your pardon.

22:46.040 --> 22:48.919
I mean, you're talking about
the man my mother loves.
I can't kill him.

22:49.120 --> 22:50.349
Yes, you can.
No, I can't.

22:50.560 --> 22:51.676
Yes, you can.
No, I can't.

22:51.880 --> 22:53.109
Yes, you can.
No, I can't.

22:53.320 --> 22:56.040
Yes, you... What is this,
a musical? Yes, you can.

22:56.560 --> 22:58.279
And I'm a gonna tell you
how you can

22:58.480 --> 23:01.279
by letting you know
what's gonna happen
if you can't.

23:01.520 --> 23:03.159
If you can't, we gonna kill you.

23:05.000 --> 23:06.798
As they say in <i>Italiano:</i>

23:07.000 --> 23:09.390
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

23:10.160 --> 23:15.440
What's that mean?
Boy, are you in it!

23:16.080 --> 23:18.037
[♪♪♪]

